SECTION 9: NVIDIA-SPECIFIC ARCHITECTURE TOOLS
================================================================================

NEMO AGENT TOOLKIT:
  Pre-built agent templates for common patterns.
  Optimized inference pipelines for NVIDIA hardware.
  Handles the plumbing: HybridAgent, ReactiveLayer, DeliberativeLayer classes.
  Sets up confidence thresholds, model routing, optimization levels.

NIM (NVIDIA INFERENCE MICROSERVICES):
  Containerized inference services for LLMs.
  10-100x faster than naive deployments.
  Features: automatic batching, KV cache, multi-GPU parallelism, load balancing.
  Used as the backend for LLM calls in agent workflows.
  LangChain integration: ChatNVIDIA(base_url="your-nim-endpoint").

NEMO GUARDRAILS:
  Safety layer that wraps any LLM with configurable rules.
  Input rails: Block jailbreaks, detect sensitive data before it reaches LLM.
  Output rails: Check for harmful content, hallucinations, policy violations.
  Configuration: YAML-based colang files, not Python code.
  Critical for production agents — can't deploy without safety checks.

ARCHITECTURE OF A FULL NVIDIA AGENT STACK:
  User → NeMo Guardrails (input check) → Hybrid Agent
  → Reactive Layer (8B NIM) or Deliberative Layer (70B NIM)
  → Tools (search, calculator, APIs)
  → Response → NeMo Guardrails (output check) → User


